'''Yamakatahiko Shrine''' (やまかたひこじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} enshrined in {{ill|lt=Takara-chō|Q11430667|WD=Q11430667|1=Takara-chō}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima|Q207309|WD=Q207309|1=Tokushima (city)}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|WD=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}.

=== History ===
Its founding period is unknown. It is regarded as a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}, though there is also a theory that the subordinate shrine Tateiwa Shrine, which manages it as a {{ill|lt=massha|Q135009906|WD=Q135009906|1=Massha}}, is the actual corresponding shrine.

It is said that a copper {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=tatara|1=UNKNOWN}} once stood in this area. In addition, {{ill|lt=Yayoi pottery|Q11487461|WD=Q11487461|1=Yayoi pottery}} and metal implements have been excavated nearby. It was also called '''Koisha''' (こひしゃ) and '''Kanaya Gongen'''. Another name is '''Kanayama Shrine'''. Under the {{ill|lt=modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|WD=Q712534|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}}, it was an unranked shrine.

=== Enshrined deity ===
* {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Kanayamahiko-no-Kami|1=UNKNOWN}}

